HB 697 Original 2026 Regular Session Geymann
Abstract: Re-creates the Dept. of Environmental Quality.
Present law (Sunset) provides that the Dept. of Environmental Quality and all the statutory
entities made a part of that department by law shall begin to terminate their operations on
July 1, 2026, and that all legislative authority for such entities shall cease as of July 1, 2027,
unless the legislature enacts a bill authorizing the re-creation of the department and its
statutory entities prior thereto.
Proposed law provides for the general re-creation of the Dept. of Environmental Quality and
its statutory entities, effective June 30, 2026, in accordance with the "sunset" law.
